Senate Commerce and Labor 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB1800
Bailey
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1800* House Bill No. 2056
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 62-3-110, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(c) A barber school or college shall use a student identification number for
students who are accruing instructional hours in order to apply for an examination. The
barber school or college shall not use a student's social security number on an hourly
report form and shall instead use the student identification number until a student is
ready to take an examination or receive a certificate of registration.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 62-3-124, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(e)
(1) A barber school or college shall use a student identification number
for applicants accruing instructional hours in order to apply for a certificate of
registration as a barber instructor. A barber school or college shall not use a
student's social security number and shall instead use the student identification
number until a student is ready to be registered.
(2) The administrator of a board-approved barber instructor training
program shall use a student identification number for a barber instructor's
biennial reporting required by subsection (b).
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 62-4-110, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
SA0664
014701
- 1 -

(g) A school of cosmetology shall use a student identification number for
applicants accruing instructional hours in order to apply for an examination. The school
of cosmetology shall not use a student's social security number on an hourly report form
and shall instead use the student identification number until a student is ready to take an
examination or receive a license.
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 62-4-114, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(e) An administrator of a board-approved instructor training program shall use
the active instructor's student identification number for reporting ongoing or initial
instructional hours required by subsections (a) and (b).
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 62-4-135, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(d) The administrator of the training required by subdivision (b)(1) shall use a
student identification number for applicants accruing instructional hours for a certificate.
The administrator shall not use a student's social security number on an hourly report
form and shall instead use the student identification number until a student is ready to
receive a certificate.
SECTION 6. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
